WEBVTT

00:26.360 --> 00:28.320
This is Fauzi Nidal.

00:28.390 --> 00:30.260
Leave a message and
I'll call you back.

00:32.159 --> 00:35.000
Fauzi, it's, uh... it's me again.
Barry.

00:35.070 --> 00:36.600
Um... Bassam.

00:36.670 --> 00:40.070
Uh, I'm not sure if you're
getting my messages,

00:40.140 --> 00:44.070
but, um, I'm coming for
my nephew's wedding.

00:44.140 --> 00:46.240
Uh, arriving tomorrow.

00:46.310 --> 00:50.580
My US cell number
should work, so, uh...

00:50.650 --> 00:52.310
so call me.

00:52.380 --> 00:55.920
It would be good to see you.

01:33.420 --> 01:38.330
Jamal, fix your button.

01:38.390 --> 01:42.030
How do you expect people to respect
you if you can't dress yourself?

01:50.440 --> 01:52.840
Jamal. Bassam.

01:52.910 --> 01:54.140
Come on, Jamal. Come out.

01:54.210 --> 01:56.910
Khaled! Khaled! Khaled!

01:56.980 --> 02:01.380
Khaled! Khaled! Khaled! Khaled!

02:01.450 --> 02:04.150
Khaled! Khaled!

02:04.220 --> 02:06.120
Wave, Jamal.

02:07.190 --> 02:10.360
Not like a girl. Wave.

02:16.460 --> 02:18.630
Jamal, go stand over there.

02:23.320 --> 02:24.680
Mr. President.

02:24.710 --> 02:27.310
My son will cut the ribbon.

02:33.410 --> 02:38.720
It is a great honor... to
be standing here with you,

02:38.790 --> 02:41.120
the good people of Ma'an.

02:49.460 --> 02:54.530
This ground, once stained
with the blood and tears

02:54.600 --> 03:01.410
of conflict, has been cleansed
by the sweat of your good work.

03:03.510 --> 03:07.680
This bridge is more than
just steel and concrete.

03:07.750 --> 03:12.750
It is a symbol that despite
our differences...

03:18.270 --> 03:20.060
Get down, Bassam!

03:38.440 --> 03:40.810
Hello, Mrs. Shapiro.

03:40.880 --> 03:43.280
I'm sorry to
call so early, Doctor, but

03:43.350 --> 03:44.650
Danny's been coughing all night.

03:44.720 --> 03:47.750
Uh, well, uh, Dr. Chang

03:47.780 --> 03:50.120
is covering my patients this week,
so let me give you his service number...

03:50.190 --> 03:53.420
I'm sure he's
fine, but I really trust you.

03:53.490 --> 03:54.620
I'm glad you trust me,

03:54.690 --> 03:58.460
but he's an excellent doctor and
I'm about to leave town, s...

03:58.530 --> 04:02.200
I get that you're busy,
but what if he has strep?

04:02.270 --> 04:06.900
No, I, uh, I
understand, I do, uh...

04:06.970 --> 04:08.940
I'll be at my office
in ten minutes.

04:09.010 --> 04:10.570
Thank you, Dr. Al Fayeed.

04:10.640 --> 04:12.440
Okay. Bye.

04:14.750 --> 04:17.050
I can't believe you're
making us go to this wedding

04:17.110 --> 04:18.850
when they're burning pictures
of Grandpa on the street.

04:18.920 --> 04:19.980
Emma, get off the Internet.

04:20.050 --> 04:23.190
And they burned down the bakery
where the wedding cake was being made.

04:25.360 --> 04:28.320
And you think this is funny?
What if they attack us?

04:28.390 --> 04:29.490
No one's attacking us.

04:29.560 --> 04:31.760
And if they do, we'll
have armed escorts.

04:31.830 --> 04:33.460
Dad's father's like a king.

04:33.530 --> 04:36.460
Em, we're royalty over there.

04:36.530 --> 04:39.100
You know, you'll be like Kate Middleton.
Just fat.

04:39.170 --> 04:40.970
Hey, don't talk to
your sister like that.

04:41.040 --> 04:41.770
Come on.

04:41.840 --> 04:43.440
What part of what I
said isn't true?

04:43.510 --> 04:45.540
- Emma...
- Aw, it's cute.

04:45.610 --> 04:47.510
Seriously, can you just
stop with the attitude

04:47.580 --> 04:49.410
and try to appreciate what an
amazing opportunity this is?

04:49.480 --> 04:50.350
Yeah.

04:50.410 --> 04:52.180
It's not just me, you know.

04:52.250 --> 04:54.020
- Dad doesn't want to go either.
- He told you that?

04:54.080 --> 04:55.520
He didn't have to.
Isn't it obvious?

04:55.580 --> 04:58.250
Why do you think he hasn't
been back in 20 years?

04:58.320 --> 05:00.490
He doesn't want to go, and
I don't want to go either.

05:00.560 --> 05:02.160
So I'm not going.

05:02.220 --> 05:04.060
You're going.

05:11.570 --> 05:12.730
That was a long run.

05:12.800 --> 05:14.640
You missed all the fun.

05:14.700 --> 05:16.500
Medical emergency.

05:16.570 --> 05:18.140
Danny Shapiro's got strep.

05:18.210 --> 05:20.440
That's why I don't give out
my cell number to patients.

05:23.510 --> 05:25.580
Sammy, clear your plate.

05:25.615 --> 05:27.580
Got to finish packing.

05:28.330 --> 05:32.000
Honey, you do realize Emma's
manifesting your negativity.

05:32.060 --> 05:35.070
Maybe on the plane ride, you
can think of something nice

05:35.130 --> 05:36.070
to tell her about your family.

05:36.105 --> 05:37.910
They're not my family.
You're my family.

05:37.945 --> 05:39.840
No, see, this is exactly
what I'm talking about.

05:39.890 --> 05:40.790
Of course she's acting out.

05:40.825 --> 05:43.030
All she hears about is how
you don't want to go.

05:43.065 --> 05:44.980
Just promise me we'll come back.

05:45.015 --> 05:46.660
What?

05:49.370 --> 05:52.940
Very funny.

05:57.430 --> 06:00.070
I told you not to take the
405... I mean, come on, who

06:00.140 --> 06:01.400
takes the 405?

06:01.470 --> 06:04.640
All right, let's
go, let's move it.

06:06.510 --> 06:08.480
Come on!

06:15.250 --> 06:18.550
Great. You happy now?

06:18.620 --> 06:19.890
We missed our flight.

06:19.960 --> 06:21.720
I'm sure there's another one.

06:21.790 --> 06:23.690
Or maybe it's a sign
from Allah that we should go

06:23.760 --> 06:26.760
to Disney World like
every other family.

06:26.830 --> 06:28.760
I'll call the airline. See
if there's another flight.

06:28.830 --> 06:31.460
- Mr. Al Fayeed?
- Yes.

06:31.495 --> 06:34.630
- Are you ready to board?
- The plane's still here?

06:34.665 --> 06:35.690
Of course.

06:35.760 --> 06:37.600
I'm sorry. Has
everyone else boarded?

06:37.660 --> 06:40.700
You are the only
passengers, sir.

06:40.770 --> 06:43.770
Your father bought all the
other seats on the plane.

06:47.910 --> 06:51.080
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

06:51.140 --> 06:53.810
Oh, wow.

06:53.880 --> 06:55.750
This is what I'm talking about.

06:57.020 --> 06:58.180
I think I like this.

06:58.215 --> 06:59.110
A whole plane?

06:59.180 --> 07:02.780
Oh, no. No, wait, wait.
All right, this one.

07:02.900 --> 07:04.880
Oh, man. Look at this.

07:04.915 --> 07:06.280
Thank you, Grandpa.

07:06.340 --> 07:08.380
Okay, guys, get up, please.

07:08.450 --> 07:09.850
These aren't our seats.

07:11.180 --> 07:13.050
Y... You're kidding, right?

07:13.120 --> 07:14.320
No, get up.

07:14.390 --> 07:16.790
We're gonna sit in the
seats that we paid for.

07:19.240 --> 07:20.300
Isn't this a little crazy?

07:20.370 --> 07:22.340
This is what's crazy.

07:22.375 --> 07:24.840
I say no to his private
jet, so he does this.

07:24.875 --> 07:27.750
And I'm... I'm not gonna be
manipulated like that.

07:27.785 --> 07:29.150
No way.

07:29.210 --> 07:32.150
Honey, your father'll
never know.

07:34.790 --> 07:36.390
Fine.

07:36.450 --> 07:38.320
Sit wherever you want.

07:47.500 --> 07:49.430
It's okay.

07:49.500 --> 07:51.330
I'll go sit with Dad.

07:51.400 --> 07:52.770
No. Stay here.

08:10.390 --> 08:13.290
I'm in the window seat.

08:38.659 --> 08:40.659
<b>Tyrant S01E01
"Pilot"</b>

08:40.695 --> 08:44.169
<i>Sync and corrected by n17t01 - addic7ed.com
webdl resync by Gianluca Belfiglio
</i>

08:58.590 --> 09:01.460
Oh.

09:01.530 --> 09:03.800
How long have I been out?

09:03.870 --> 09:05.470
Couple hours.

09:05.540 --> 09:06.770
Mmm.

09:06.840 --> 09:09.640
So no turning back, huh?

09:09.710 --> 09:15.510
If it makes a difference, I'm
really happy we're doing this.

09:15.580 --> 09:19.250
Well, I'm happy when you're happy.

09:20.680 --> 09:23.450
See, I see a real
opportunity here.

09:23.520 --> 09:26.460
To finally sit down
with your father.

09:26.520 --> 09:28.290
Tell him everything you've
been carrying around

09:28.360 --> 09:30.430
in your head all these years.

09:32.590 --> 09:36.430
Yeah, you don't know my father.

09:36.500 --> 09:38.430
I know you.

09:38.500 --> 09:40.470
I see you're awake.

09:40.540 --> 09:42.500
Yes.

09:42.570 --> 09:43.640
What do you have there?

09:43.710 --> 09:47.210
Dom Pérignon Rosé
OenothÃ¨que 1990.

09:47.280 --> 09:49.910
Your brother, Jamal, insisted
we have it on board for you.

09:52.550 --> 09:55.350
To your brother, Jamal.

09:56.890 --> 09:59.250
To my brother.

10:31.690 --> 10:35.310
Why you didn't get me?
My wife just called.

10:35.350 --> 10:37.660
My brother's landing
in ten minutes.

10:42.600 --> 10:44.930
Go inside...

